p revenue us  billion  operating income us  million  profit us  million  total assets us  billion  number of employees   subsidiaries cineform replay splice website wwwgoprocom gopro inc marketed as gopro and sometimes stylised as gopro is an american technology company founded in  by nick woodman it manufactures eponymous action cameras and develops its own mobile apps and videoediting software founded as woodman labs inc the company eventually focused on the connected sports genre developing its line of action cameras and later video editing software it also developed a quadcopter drone karma released in october  in october  before the release of karma quadcopter drone gopro released the gopro hero  and hero  session contents  history  corporate actions  ipo  product lines  hero cameras  gopro karma  gopro karma grip  accessories  video editing  content company  hd hero cameras  products  hero cameras  mm  digital  digital   digital   digital wide  hd    led  specifications  hero  hero  hero  hero  herolcd  hero  hero  gopro karma drone  gopro omni  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded by nick woodman in  he was motivated by a  surfing trip to australia in which he was hoping to capture quality action photos but could not because amateur photographers could not get close enough or buy quality equipment at reasonable prices his desire for a camera system that could capture the professional angles inspired the gopro name woodman raised a portion of his initial capital by selling bead and shell belts for under us  from his vw van and later fashionable camera straps he also received over  from his parents to invest in the business in  the company sold its first camera system which used  mm film digital still and video cameras were later introduced as of update a fixedlens hd video camera with a wide degree lens was available two or more can be paired to create  video on june   the company announced the appointment of former microsoft executive tony bates as president reporting directly to woodman in january  gopro partnered with periscope for live streaming after growing the number of employees by more than  in  the company responded to weak sales in the fourth quarter by cutting about  of its workforce  workers in january  at its peak a share of gopro was valued at  but on september   only  in november  the company announced it was laying off an additional  employees in an effort to reduce costs the company also announced that president tony bates would be stepping down at the end of  corporate actionsedit on march   gopro acquired cineform the acquisition included the cineform  video codec used in the film slumdog millionaire the company claimed that the codec makes hd and d editing faster and more convenient without sacrificing image quality it was incorporated in the companys d hero system shortly after the acquisition in march  gopro issued a dmca takedown notice to website digitalrevcom which had posted a review of its product citing trademark use as a breach of copyright this notice was retracted  days later citing erroneous enforcement on february   gopro spent  million and acquired two startups namely stupeflix and vemory for their video editing tools replay and splice ipoedit on february   gopro submitted a confidential filing for an initial public offering ipo with the securities and exchange commission sec on may   gopro filed its s with the sec without specifying the number of shares or their price the company stated that they hoped to raise at least  million through the sale of shares using the money to pay off debt in full  million as of march   and to acquire or invest in complementary businesses technologies or assets they said that they planned to list on the nasdaq stock exchange using the symbol gpro the expected price range was  to  a share on june   gopro sold  million shares to initial investors at  per share totaling m at the ipo price the company was valued at  billion  percent of those shares were allotted to loyal a technology platform that allows small investors to participate an important reason for gopros decision to go public was the potential to become a media company to generate additional revenue from the content its cameras create product linesedit hero camerasedit woodman worked on his first camera for two years after founding the company eventually introducing the gopro mm hero in september  at san diegos action sports retailer trade show in its first year gopro sold  worth of products in  the company introduced its first digital hero with  second video capability and generated  in revenue the following year gopro sales quadrupled to  million in  the company was selling the hero in editions of different colors it was capable of filming in  aspect ratio supporting k uhd video and mp still photographs the hero was introduced on  september  gopro karma  gopro karma gripedit gopro drone karma the gopro karma is gopros consumer dronecitation needed in  gopro entered into discussions with dji for a private label model built with the gopro branding after the failure of these negotiations gopro entered into an agreement with d robotics dr for a similar partnership based on drs flight controllers dr failed to meet their agreed upon timelines as a result gopro took full control of the development process in mid scheduled to be released early  the gopro karma project was delayed several times before the gopro karma was announced with an introduction date of october   the karma was released along with newer models of the hero and session cameras and features a removable handheld stabilizer gimbal integrated into the design after a few customers complained about power failure during operation gopro recalled karma drones and gave customers full refunds in february  gopro relaunched the karma drone accessoriesedit gopro produces various mounting accessories for its cameras including a way mount suction cup chest harness jawstype flexible clamp dog harness surfing mount etc video editingedit the company developed gopro studio simple video editing software to edit camera footage with v released in october  it was reported that gopro intended to also become a content provider also with a new app for the hero called gopro quik to share and edit videos easier content companyedit in april  gopro was listed by adweek as one of the top  best brand channels on youtube based on a combination of views shares comments and overall engagement content is uploaded daily an additional source of revenue for the company as part of its transformation to a media company in  gopro created additional channels with gopro content on youtube virgin america and xbox live this was extended to the playstation network in  hd hero camerasedit as of october update gopro sells three fixedlens cameras two without viewfinders and one including a touchscreen viewfinder a bit lcd on the front of the camera allows access to its menu system which is controlled by the front and top shutter buttons the hero black have dimensions of  mm ×  mm ×  mm and weighs  grams  grams with housing still images from  to  megapixels can be captured the cameras are sold with a clear polycarbonate hd housing with a glass lens that is rated shockproof and waterproof to  feet  m with a quickrelease buckle on the top and threads at the bottom to attach to all of the gopro mounts the housing has metal buttons that connect to the cameras controls and has a skeleton backdoor option to allow audio recording when the camera is used with a mount but without the need to be watertight or shockproofnonprimary source needed productsedit hero camerasedit mmedit the mm camera model  became available on april   it had dimensions of  by  inches  by  mm and weighed  pounds  g it included the camera a clear case with quick release a camera strap and ski glove adapter lash it could pivot on the fly and be functional to a depth in water of about  feet  m it was described