ng competition from much cheaper action cameras while the competitors may not be able to match gopros quality they provide the same functionality at a much cheaper price then there is also the execution problem last holiday season gopro managed to botch the release of its muchawaited hero  line of cameras as well as the karma drone manufacturing issues led to delay in the delivery of hero  black camera during the allimportant holiday season more importantly gopro was forced to recall its muchhyped karma drones due to technical issues the recall was announced after gopro discovered that karma drones were prone to crashing midflight due to a sudden loss of power the recall did a great damage to gopros brand name and this was not the first big launch which gopro had flubbed even hero  launch didnt go as planned gopro was forced to slash its price within few months of the launch and take a hit of millions of dollars in inventory writedowns product diversification while action cameras remain gopros main revenue source the company has been diversifying into other product markets apart from the karma drone gopro has also launched subscription service for photo and video editing and sharing diversification will help to increase gopros total addressable market and reduce the business risk however both karma and the subscription service didnt have a perfect start the recall of karma during the allimportant holiday season was a big blow to the brand and the timing didnt help either given the negative brand image and strong competition from chinese drone manufacturer dji gopro will have to invest significant time and money in the drone to make it appeal to customers once again karma drone lacked several features such as collision avoidance and follow me which are now staple features in most of the drones further the action camera company announced the pilot launch of fusion k spherical camera fusion is a degree spherical camera thats supposed to allow you to reframe images in d shots and see fullfield of view in vr vr is a rapidly growing market which could be a big opportunity for gopro according to statistacom vr hardware market is expected to grow from  billion in  to  billion in  while karma was diversification into an industry in which gopro didnt have much experience fusion is a perfect example of product extension in gopros core business in which the company has considerable expertise gopro stock remains a risky bet gopros recent launches have failed to live up to their promise till now with the growth in action camera market slowing down gopro needs another product to drive its growth the companys decision to enter the vr market through fusion camera is a good move though it might be some time before it has any impact on gopros top line given the challenges gopro stock remains a risky longterm bet check out our daily stocks to buy for daily trading ideas looking for great tech stocks check out amigobulls top stocks to buy which have beaten the nasdaq by around  we also have our set of top picks from the auto sector which have beaten the sp  by over    share this article via email share this article on twitter share this article on facebook share this article on linkedin share this article on googleplus is this article helpful      more on gopro stock kumar abhishek   on amigobulls  follow comments on this article and gpro stock post bullish neutral bearish do share this awesome post gopro stock articles microsoft corporation gopro inc and valeant pharmaceuticals intl  todays technical trading ideas micron technology inc stock valeant pharmaceuticals intl inc and gopro inc  technical stock trading ideas for today is gopro stock a good buy ahead of gopro inc q  earnings gpro stock apple stock gopro inc and fitbit  technical stock trading ideas for today is gopro inc gpro stock a value play or value trap near its alltime low gopro stock is at all time low should you buy now gpro news tell your story in one tap with gopro quikstories 