an headquarters san mateo california us area served worldwide key people nick woodman ceo tony bates president products action camera video editing software mobile app revenue us  billion  operating income us  million  profit us  million  total assets us  billion  number of employees   subsidiaries cineform replay splice website wwwgoprocom gopro inc marketed as gopro and sometimes stylised as gopro is an american technology company founded in  by nick woodman it manufactures eponymous action cameras and develops its own mobile apps and videoediting software founded as woodman labs inc the company eventually focused on the connected sports genre developing its line of action cameras and later video editing software it also developed a quadcopter drone karma released in october  in october  before the release of karma quadcopter drone gopro released the gopro hero  and hero  session contents  history  corporate actions  ipo  product lines  hero cameras  gopro karma  gopro karma grip  accessories  video editing  content company  hd hero cameras  products  hero cameras  mm  digital  digital   digital   digital wide  hd    led  specifications  hero  hero  hero  hero  herolcd  hero  hero  gopro karma drone  gopro omni  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded by nick woodman in  he was motivated by a  surfing trip to australia in which he was hoping to capture quality action photos but could not because amateur photographers could not get close enough or buy quality equipment at reasonable prices his desire for a camera system that could capture the professional angles inspired the gopro name woodman raised a portion of his initial capital by selling bead and shell belts for under us  from his vw van and later fashionable camera straps he also received over  from his parents to invest in the business in  the company sold its first camera system which used  mm film digital still and video cameras were later introduced as of update a fixedlens hd video camera with a wide degree lens was available two or more can be paired to create  video on june   the company announced the appointment of former microsoft executive tony bates as president reporting directly to woodman in january  gopro partnered with periscope for live streaming after growing the number of employees by more than  in  the company responded to weak sales in the fourth quarter by cutting about  of its workforce  workers in january  at its peak a share of gopro was valued at  but on september   only  in november  the company announced it was laying off an additional  employees in an effort to reduce costs the company also announced that president tony bates would be stepping down at the end of  corporate actionsedit on march   gopro acquired cineform the acquisition included the cineform  video codec used in the film slumdog millionaire the company claimed that the codec makes hd and d editing faster and more convenient without sacrificing image quality it was incorporated in the companys d hero system shortly after the acquisition in march  gopro issued a dmca takedown notice to website digitalrevcom which had posted a review of its product citing trademark use as a breach of copyright this notice was retracted  days later citing erroneous enforcement on february   gopro spent  million and acquired two startups namely stupeflix and vemory for their video editing tools replay and splice ipoedit on february   gopro submitted a confidential filing for an initial public offering ipo with the securities and exchange commission sec on may   gopro filed its s with the sec without specifying the number of shares or their price the company stated that they hoped to raise at least  million through the sale of shares using the money to pay off debt in full  million as of march   and to acquire or invest in complementary businesses technologies or assets they said that they planned to list on the nasdaq stock exchange using the symbol gpro the expect