ry runtime during recording than hero black edition they both use the same batteries the difference in runtime depends on the resolutionfps combination and whether wifi and gopro mobile application are used during recording the difference in runtime increases as the fps is lowered and the additional functions are deactivated on both cameras the battery runtime of hero silver edition is similar to the battery runtime of hero and hero the hero hd camera was awarded the  technology  engineering emmy award for its contribution to television heroedit gopro hero  silver edition in september  gopro announced the hero available in black edition and silver edition which replace their respective hero generation predecessors the hero session a budget camera was also announced the hero black edition still has a  mp cmos and a f fixed maximum aperture and focus free it adds bluetooth connectivity highlight tag protune available for photo and a new processor claimed by gopro to be twice as fast as that of the hero black edition doubling the frame rates in most resolutions the hero black edition can record k uhd video × at a frame rate of   and  fps in superview mode k is only possible at  fps many other rates and resolutions are available the hero black edition still shoots stills at a maximum of mp with a maximum burst rate of  fps with wifi disabled at k gopro claims the hero black edition battery life to be  minutes increasing to a maximum of h  at p the hero black battery is in a different form factor than its predecessors initial sidebyside comparisons of hero and hero black edition video results suggest that the newer model has more detail at long range and similar performance at close range the hero silver edition is basically a hero black edition with the addition of a micro speaker builtin touch screen display protune for photo and highlight tag the first gopro with this a lower clocked cortexa and missing the black editions integrated analogtodigital converter which sup