ducts  hero cameras  mm  digital  digital   digital   digital wide  hd    led  specifications  hero  hero  hero  hero  herolcd  hero  hero  gopro karma drone  gopro omni  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded by nick woodman in  he was motivated by a  surfing trip to australia in which he was hoping to capture quality action photos but could not because amateur photographers could not get close enough or buy quality equipment at reasonable prices his desire for a camera system that could capture the professional angles inspired the gopro name woodman raised a portion of his initial capital by selling bead and shell belts for under us  from his vw van and later fashionable camera straps he also received over  from his parents to invest in the business in  the company sold its first camera system which used  mm film digital still and video cameras were later introduced as of update a fixedlens hd video camera with a wide degree lens was available two or more can be paired to create  video on june   the company announced the appointment of former microsoft executive tony bates as president reporting directly to woodman in january  gopro partnered with periscope for live streaming after growing the number of employees by more than  in  the company responded to weak sales in the fourth quarter by cutting about  of its workforce  workers in january  at its peak a share of gopro was valued at  but on september   only  in november  the company announced it was laying off an additional  employees in an effort to reduce costs the company also announced that president tony bates would be stepping down at the end of  corporate actionsedit on march   gopro acquired cineform the acquisition included the cineform  video codec used in the film slumdog millionaire the company claimed that the codec makes hd and d editing faster and more convenient without sacrificing image quality it was incorporated in the companys d hero system shortly after the 